meta.name: Hyundai Country Calendar
meta.description: Take a look at iconic rural Kiwi life in New Zealand's longest running television series! Made with the support of NZ on Air.

videos.title: Post Production
videos.overview: A sheep farming family builds a business salvaging broken vineyard posts and recycling them for farm fences, saving hundreds of thousands of posts from landfill.

videos.title: Call of the Land
videos.overview: A 17-year-old woman leaves school and opts to follow her dream to go farming. Louisa says everyone was surprised at first, but they now support her choice.

videos.title: Love the Life
videos.overview: A husband and wife farm with a love for each other and of the land. She's a city girl turned farmer, and together they breed horses, train working dogs and ride endurance.

videos.title: To Feed an Island
videos.overview: On Great Barrier Island, a market gardening couple grow top-quality heritage fruit and veges using organic methods. They've had to be inventive and hard-working to survive.

videos.title: The Whole Hog
videos.overview: A couple expand their free range pig farm in Wairarapa with the help of Hong Kong backers, turning heritage breeds into pork much sought-after by chefs.

videos.title: Out the Back
videos.overview: A couple uses traditional draught horses for all their farm tasks on a Canterbury high country station. The horses pull the supply wagon for the team working the annual autumn muster.

videos.title: Taking Charge
videos.overview: A young King Country couple take over the running of the parents' farm on the banks of the Whanganui River. They produce woollen baby blankets from the lambs' first shear.

videos.title: Mussel Bound
videos.overview: As a young scientist, John Young began investigating if mussels could be farmed and 40 years later he's still on the water, leading New Zealand's second-biggest mussel farming company.

videos.title: Peak Production
videos.overview: A family in the Canterbury high country prepare for their annual deer auction, while entertaining trophy hunters from the USA, and being part of a traveling theatre troupe.

videos.title: Cray Brothers
videos.overview: Two brothers find success chasing crayfish off the wild Marlborough coast. They export them live, providing jobs for their small community, as well as farming beef and growing grapes.

videos.title: Mighty Manuka
videos.overview: A look at a Manuka honey business in Gisborne.

videos.title: Banana Republic
videos.overview: A family growing all their food off the land who love bananas is featured.

videos.title: Motu Magic
videos.overview: A couple buy their first farm and find success.

videos.title: Lavender for Luck
videos.overview: Following two generations of a family running a lavender farm.

videos.title: Protein Power
videos.overview: A family attempt to start growing quinoa, a crop that few New Zealanders have been successful with.

videos.title: Planting A Future
videos.overview: An East Coast whanau sets about securing their family's future by restoring their lands, through partnership with a new farm carbon-forestry venture.

videos.title: Flat Out
videos.overview: A North Island farmer moves south to manage a government-owned farm on the edge of Fiordland National Park, making changes to improve the farming system.

videos.title: All At Sea
videos.overview: A Rakiura Stewart Island family have all made their living on the sea, catching crays or diving for paua, & the next generation is now becoming an expert fisher.

videos.title: Sale Day
videos.overview: A farmer on a Banks Peninsula coastal property raises lambs for their on-farm auction, while his wife draws inspiration from their land for her paintings.

videos.title: Tane to Tangaroa
videos.overview: A Bay of Plenty whnau Mori runs an oyster farm, providing jobs for local rangatahi and delicious kaimoana for people passing through their coastal village.

videos.title: Go With the Flow
videos.overview: A Taup couple milks sheep on their first farm, on the shores of the lake, treading lightly on the land & protecting the water that enters the lake.

videos.title: Changing Ways
videos.overview: An award-winning South Auckland couple builds a team to embrace new farming and conservation practices to future-proof their dairy, sheep & beef operations.

videos.title: Shear Joy
videos.overview: After many years working away from the land, a couple return to take over the family farms where they were brought up and develop new outlets for their lambswool.

videos.title: The Science of the Lambs
videos.overview: A former AgResearch staff member gets his own farm & puts what he's learned into practice by taking a scientific approach to how he runs it.

videos.title: Cherry Picking
videos.overview: A Central Otago orchardist runs an export cherry business, built up from childhood paper-run savings and saves second-rate cherries from going to waste.

videos.title: Big Day Out
videos.overview: Two shepherding brothers on a vast East Coast hill country station go on to buy the property and draw the community together for their traditional on-farm sale.

videos.title: Growing a Dream
videos.overview: A Gisborne family grows citrus & apples for the domestic & export markets, processing it in their new packhouse, and providing work for locals & travellers.

videos.title: Hit The Ground Running
videos.overview: A third generation vet with a passion for everything equine runs a busy horse reproduction business with her husband on their Manawat family farm.

videos.title: Hive of Industry
videos.overview: Two young bee-keeping brothers in Manawat have built up their honey business through hard graft, inventiveness and with timber milled from the family farm.

videos.title: An Apple a Day
videos.overview: A Motueka family grows heritage varieties of apples, pears & plums on their organic orchard, selling the fruit and producing cider vinegars, juices & tonics.

videos.title: Cows and Flowers
videos.overview: An American family moves to Otago, creates a boutique dairy farm, grow flowers and sells all their produce direct to the local community.

videos.title: Helping Hand
videos.overview: A retired Canterbury engineer buys a rundown apple orchard and converts it to organics, running it with the help of his family who also run a flower business.

videos.title: A Different Light
videos.overview: A manager takes a job on a farm newly bought by an Austrian business couple who know little about farming, but bring a new approach to how the farm is run.

videos.title: On a Roll
videos.overview: A Rangitikei couple manages three big hill country sheep and beef farms while starting a new business making nutritious dog food for working dogs.

videos.title: Fisherman's Friend
videos.overview: A Northland fisherman with a passion for the industry helps other fishers navigate changes to regulations and looks after their mental wellbeing.

videos.title: Swede As
videos.overview: A Southland family whose farm was saved by them growing swedes, and who now have built a thriving business from their humble roadside vegetable stall.

videos.title: Steak and Eggs
videos.overview: A North Canterbury couple produces free range eggs, beef cattle and sheep and have started their own butchery, all built up since they moved here from Germany.

videos.title: Family Tradition
videos.overview: Two Marlborough brothers make their mark on their diverse family businesses which include cherries, vineyards and making hay for horses.

videos.title: Growing Together
videos.overview: Two American brothers enlist the help of a woman with farming expertise to create a farm & garden to provide food for their local community near Upper Hutt.

videos.title: Taste of Place
videos.overview: A Marlborough family grows grapes and makes new world wines using old world methods of planting and harvesting by the moon.

videos.title: Cracking into it
videos.overview: A couple with a love of the ocean, establishes a free-range egg farm overlooking the sea in Southland, to help realise their dreams of one day sailing away.

videos.title: Seeds of Growth
videos.overview: A Canterbury farming family grows crops to harvest the seeds, which are then used by gardeners and farmers all around the world to plant their own crops.

videos.title: Jersey Girls
videos.overview: A Waikato family have been milking Jersey cows for nearly 100 years and now sell their own brand of organic milk and yogurt, as well as growing strawberries.

videos.title: Post Production
videos.overview: A sheep farming family builds a business salvaging broken vineyard posts & recycling them for farm fences, saving hundreds of thousands of posts from landfill.

videos.title: Next Generation
videos.overview: A family farming sheep and cattle diversifies into the wellness market, turning their wool into felted exercise mats as part of their family succession plan.

videos.title: Flippin' Genius
videos.overview: A Marlborough couple re-invents the way oysters are farmed and exports their invention to the world.

videos.title: Future Whenua
videos.overview: An iwi-led community garden uses mtauranga Mori and permaculture principles to grow food for local people and connect them with the land.

videos.title: Born to Run
videos.overview: A woman rounds up and rehomes wild horses, and also rescues, rehabilitates and races neglected miniature ponies from her Far North farm.

videos.title: Home Sweet Home
videos.overview: A Wairarapa family breeds their sheep flock to be wool-less, and adds a timber mill, a thriving rural caf and a chocolate factory to their coastal station.

videos.title: Going Bananas
videos.overview: A Northland couple grows bananas and other tropical plants, finding the perfect varieties for the local climate, sharing their knowledge with others.

videos.title: Island Time
videos.overview: A resourceful couple raises cattle on family land in Samoa, employing locals & using the meat &amp; other local produce at their guest house for tourists.

videos.title: Hard Graft
videos.overview: A Kpiti family runs one of the few nurseries that supplies commercial vineyards with baby vines, as well as growing blackberries and running cattle.

videos.title: Green Goodness
videos.overview: A Southland family with a novel approach to dairying, keeps their cows in barns over winter, feeds them homegrown hay, and herds them using a phone app.

videos.title: Awesome Foursome
videos.overview: A tight-knit Canterbury family perfect their on-farm genetics to breed premium bulls and quality sheep that are sought after by buyers.

videos.title: In the Hunt
videos.overview: A hunter & predator-trapper shares his passion for conservation with communities & farmers, while his wife teaches young farmers at the local college.

videos.title: Wrapped in Wool
videos.overview: A woman runs a flock of coloured sheep near Nelson, producing many shades for sale, and running craft workshops to inspire others with her love of wool.

videos.title: Pecking Order
videos.overview: Two young entrepreneurs take a run at rural life, focussing on connecting farmers and consumers & building a community around their egg farm.

videos.title: A Natural Flow
videos.overview: A West Otago family works with nature on their large organic farm and sells their beef and lamb direct to customers.

videos.title: Big is Beautiful
videos.overview: A couple combines their two passions of running the family dairy farm and breeding Clydesdale horses for showing, ploughing and harness work.

videos.title: Walk on the Wild Side
videos.overview: A Wairarapa family hosts visitors on the North Island's original farm walk and develops two neighbouring properties to support the next generation's farming future.

videos.title: New Pastures
videos.overview: A love of farming discovered in prison has led a former inmate to become an award-winning manager of a Waikato dairy farm, while sharing his story with rangatahi.

videos.title: Hog Wild
videos.overview: A Timaru couple passionate about pigs, produce high-quality, free-range pork, for restaurants and supermarkets around the country.

videos.title: Kai School
videos.overview: A Southland woman shares her knowledge of kaimoana gathering and hunting with others wanting to connect with the whenua, while a global audience follows her on TikTok.

videos.title: Tide After Tide
videos.overview: A young family at 90 Mile Beach is ensuring sustainably harvested and processed mussels continue to be a way of life for their Far North community.

videos.title: Sure-Footed
videos.overview: A family with deep roots to their King Country property pursues their passion for breeding Arabian horses and hosting endurance rides on their sheep and beef farm.

videos.title: Bee Kind
videos.overview: A Far North family of beekeepers are hands-on with their business from working with nature, through to packing, marketing and selling honey to their local community.

videos.title: Sam the Trap Man
videos.overview: A trapper and conservation worker helps farmers control predators on their land while revitalising the natve whio population on the North Island's East Coast.

videos.title: Rock Solid
videos.overview: A Canterbury high country family runs a diverse farming operation, including deer, a breed of lamb that's renowned for its taste and texture, and a new agri-tourism venture.

videos.title: Flour to the People
videos.overview: A central Canterbury cropping farmer, keen to have more control over the grains he grows, has built his own stone mill and grinds specialty flour using traditional methods.

videos.title: Tight Knit Family
videos.overview: A Southland family breeds strong wool sheep for top-quality yarn, with one of their daughters using the wool-clip to create jerseys that are sold through a farm-gate business.

videos.title: Robots in the Shed
videos.overview: A Manawatu family has robots milking their dairy cows, allowing each cow to choose when they're milked over 24-hours, and freeing up time for the farmers to do other things.

videos.title: Sweet Resilience
videos.overview: A Northland couple escapes life in the big smoke to produce commercial quantities of subtropical fruit, making a positive contribution to the challenges of a warming climate.

videos.title: All Wrapped Up
videos.overview: A Southland deer farmer has developed a natural, edible alternative to plastic for wrapping baleage, and hopes the innovation will fund his dream of owning a high-country farm.

videos.title: Big Country
videos.overview: A couple finds their sheep and beef farm isn't paying its way, so they switch to regenerative farming, focus on soil health, and their finances start to improve.

videos.title: Texas Gold
videos.overview: A Bay of Plenty hapu develops flourishing kiwifruit orchards and dairy farms, returning its people to land previously confiscated by the Crown.

videos.title: Nutting It Out
videos.overview: A Christchurch couple wanting a change after the earthquakes buy a hazelnut orchard and turn their hand to creating an artisan range from their nuts and some grown by others.

videos.title: Kumara Country
videos.overview: A Northland kumara growing couple bounces back after being hit hard by Cyclone Gabrielle and now employs thirty staff.

videos.title: Yakety Yak
videos.overview: A Nelson vet farms a herd of Himalayan yaks along with his red deer, and juggles care of his own animals with his veterinary work around the district.

videos.title: In the Deep End
videos.overview: A new generation takes over an historic Rangitikei sheep station, employing both young workers and old hands, and creating a farm walk to add further income.

videos.title: Soil to Oil
videos.overview: An olive grower takes an evidence-based approach to producing oil that is full of flavour and health benefits, focusing on enriching the soil on his Martinborough grove.

videos.title: Super Grass
videos.overview: A Southland family diversifies into growing medicinal cannabis on their sheep farm, where they've bred stud animals for generations.

videos.title: Queen of the Herd
videos.overview: A self-taught cheese maker and lover of goats milks her own herd, making artisan cheeses and sharing her knowledge through tours and cheese making classes.

videos.title: Go For Gold
videos.overview: A Bay of Plenty family continues to lead the way, growing gold kiwifruit on their orchard with the use of cutting-edge technology and careful soil management.

videos.title: A Capital Idea
videos.overview: A couple farms sheep and cattle on the exposed, steep hills west of Wellington, and sells their meat under their own label to restaurants and direct to customers.

videos.title: Hollow Hill
videos.overview: A couple raise Perendales and coloured sheep on rugged cave country in the Waikato, creating knitting yarns from the wool, and bringing the next generation home to farm.

videos.title: Wahine Ahuwhenua
videos.overview: An award-winning farm manager and her wife are challenging stereotypes by running two large sheep and beef stations in Central Hawke's Bay.

videos.title: Passing the Reins
videos.overview: A high country family keeps alive the traditions of its annual autumn cattle muster, as the next generation starts to put their mark on the remote Marlborough station.

videos.title: Happy Campers
videos.overview: A family realise their dream of owning a farm and now practice natural horsemanship and share their love of horses and the land with others on their Whanganui property.

videos.title: Oil Fields
videos.overview: A Taranaki dairy farming family diversifies into raising Gotland sheep, and growing paddocks of Mnuka to distil into oil for balms, gels and health products.

videos.title: Room to Grow
videos.overview: A couple swap the corporate life to become homesteaders on a small block of land in Horowhenua, growing mushrooms, making specialty food products and raising a few animals.

videos.title: Taranaki Prime
videos.overview: A farming couple pioneers a field-to-fork co-op producing premium beef and lamb with fewer food miles, and selling local meat to local people.

videos.title: Waste Not
videos.overview: A Hawke's Bay woman runs a successful export business turning animal by-products into health supplements and beauty products, along with farming her own cattle.

videos.title: Fabric of the Land
videos.overview: A back-country Marlborough farm sells fine wool to Norsewear, a heritage clothing company with a dynamic new owner who sees a bright future for the fibre.

videos.title: Growing Change
videos.overview: A northern Hawke's Bay station manager helps Ngti Phauwera develop its land and people's future prospects through farming, orcharding and tourism.

videos.title: Good Fellers
videos.overview: A southern bushman turns woodlots into timber and wilding pines into biofuel, and hunts feral deer, turning them into restaurant fare.

videos.title: Breeding Business
videos.overview: A Waikato woman with a passion for genetics, runs a top Coopworth sheep stud on rugged coastal country, using scientific testing to produce hardy, parasite-tolerant sheep.

videos.title: In Grandad's Footsteps
videos.overview: We revisit a North Canterbury school-leaver who followed her dream to go farming; Ten years on and married with two kids, the couple is thriving on the land.
